Items aus einem ME speichern und abrufen
content:
os.loadAPI("ocs/apis/sensor")
sen = sensor.wrap("top")
s = sen.getTargets()
 
function getS()
    for v, k in pairs(s) do
        if k.Name == "ME Wireless Access Point" then   
            target = v
        end
    end
    sleep(0.5)
    return target
end

target = getS()

if target then
    s1 = sen.getTargetDetails(target)
    print("Items in ME System:")
    for _, item in pairs(s1.Items) do 
        local displayName = item.Name or "Unknown Item"
        local size = item.Size or 0
		local file = fs.open("List", "a")
        file.write(displayName .. " = " .. size .. "\n")
        file.close()
    end
end

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------


-- Öffne die Datei im Lesemodus
local file = fs.open("List", "r")

-- Überprüfe, ob die Datei erfolgreich geöffnet wurde
if file then
    -- Initialisiere eine Tabelle zum Speichern der Itemnamen und ihrer Werte
    local itemTable = {}

    -- Iteriere über jede Zeile in der Datei
    while true do
        local line = file.readLine() -- Lese eine Zeile aus der Datei

        -- Überprüfe, ob die Zeile existiert (Ende der Datei erreicht)
        if not line then
            break
        end

        -- Teile die Zeile in Itemnamen und Wert auf
        local itemName, itemValue = line:match("([^=]+)%s*=%s*(%d+)")

        -- Überprüfe, ob der Name und Wert gültig sind
        if itemName and itemValue then
            -- Füge das Item zur Tabelle hinzu
            itemTable[itemName] = tonumber(itemValue)
        end
    end

    -- Schließe die Datei
    file.close()

    -- Jetzt kannst du auf die Werte zugreifen, z.B.:
    print("Adjustable Emitter:", itemTable["Adjustable Emitter"])
    print("Solars:", itemTable["Solars"])
    print("HVs:", itemTable["HVs"])
else
    print("Fehler beim Öffnen der Datei")
end

import pymem

class SCMemory(pymem.Pymem):

    pClassLoader = 0
    JavaClassArray = 0

    def GetClassLoaderAndArray(self):
        mov_rax_qword_737FC700 = self.PatternScan("jvm.dll", "48 8B 05 ?? ?? ?? ?? 48 85 C0 74 ?? 48 8B 50 ?? 48 85 D2")
        self.pClassLoader = self.GetAbsoluteAddress(mov_rax_qword_737FC700, 3, 7)
        self.JavaClassArray = self.read_ulonglong(self.pClassLoader + 0x28)

    def GetAbsoluteAddress(self, ptr: int, offset: int, size: int) -> int:
        return ptr + self.read_int(ptr + offset) + size

    def PatternScan(self, module_name, pattern) -> int:
        module = pymem.process.module_from_name(self.process_handle, module_name)

        pattern_bytes_str = ""
        for byte in pattern.split(" "):
            if byte == "?" or byte == "??":
                pattern_bytes_str += "."
            else:
                pattern_bytes_str += "\\x" + byte

        pattern_bytes = bytes(pattern_bytes_str, "utf-8")

        value = pymem.pattern.pattern_scan_module(self.process_handle, module, pattern_bytes)
        if value is None:
            value = 0

        return value

    def FindJavaClassInstance(self, query):
        klass = sc.read_ulonglong(self.JavaClassArray + 0x30)  # first klass

        while klass:
            klass_symbol = sc.read_ulonglong(klass + 0x58)
            klass_name = sc.read_string(klass_symbol + 0x6, sc.read_short(klass_symbol))  # short - string len
            if klass_name == query:
                return klass
            klass = sc.read_ulonglong(klass + 0x78)  # next class

    def FindClassInstance(self, query):
        klass = sc.read_ulonglong(sc.read_ulonglong(self.pClassLoader) + 0x30)  # first klass

        while klass:
            klass_symbol = sc.read_ulonglong(klass + 0x58)
            klass_name = sc.read_string(klass_symbol + 0x6, sc.read_short(klass_symbol))  # short - string len
            if klass_name == query:
                return klass
            klass = sc.read_ulonglong(klass + 0x78)  # next class


sc = SCMemory("stalcraftw.exe")
sc.GetClassLoaderAndArray()

fl = open("dmp.txt", "w")

#Java Classes
klass = sc.read_ulonglong(sc.JavaClassArray + 0x30)  # first klass

while klass:
    klass_symbol = sc.read_ulonglong(klass + 0x58)
    klass_name = sc.read_string(klass_symbol + 0x6, sc.read_short(klass_symbol))  # short - string len
    print(klass_name)
    fl.write(klass_name + "\n")
    klass = sc.read_ulonglong(klass + 0x78)

#Other classes
klass = sc.read_ulonglong(sc.read_ulonglong(sc.pClassLoader) + 0x30)

while klass:
    klass_symbol = sc.read_ulonglong(klass + 0x58)
    klass_name = sc.read_string(klass_symbol + 0x6, sc.read_short(klass_symbol))
    print(klass_name)
    fl.write(klass_name + "\n")
    klass = sc.read_ulonglong(klass + 0x78)

title: Remote Control Script
content:
local cmp = require("component")
local ir = cmp.ir_remote_control
local term = require("term")
local event = require("event")

local brake = 1
local throttle = 0
local increment = 0.1

function increaseBrake()
  if (brake <= 1) then
    brake = brake + increment
    ir.setIndependentBrake(brake)
    ir.setBrake(brake)
  end
end

function decreaseBrake()
  if (brake > 0) then
    brake = brake - increment
    ir.setIndependentBrake(brake)
    ir.setBrake(brake)
  end
end

function setReverser()
   if (throttle > 0) then
     ir.setReverser(100)
   elseif (throttle < 0) then
     ir.setReverser(-100)
   else
     ir.setReverser(0)
   end
end

function increaseThrottle()
  if (throttle <= 1) then
    throttle = throttle + increment
    setReverser()
    local actualThrottle = throttle
    if actualThrottle < 0 then actualThrottle = actualThrottle * -1 end
    ir.setThrottle(actualThrottle)
  end
end

function decreaseThrottle()
  if (throttle > -1) then
    throttle = throttle - increment
    setReverser()
    local actualThrottle = throttle
    if actualThrottle < 0 then actualThrottle = actualThrottle * -1 end
    ir.setThrottle(actualThrottle)
  end
end

function zeroBrake()
  brake = 0
  ir.setIndependentBrake(brake)
  ir.setBrake(brake)
end

function zeroThrottle()
  throttle = 0
  setReverser()
  ir.setThrottle(throttle)
end

function fullStop()
  throttle = 0
  brake = 1
  setReverser()
  ir.setBrake(brake)
  ir.setIndependentBrake(brake)
  ir.setThrottle(throttle)
end

term.clear()
print("*** WARNING ***")
print("Make sure train has come to complete stop before continuing.")
print("Press 'E' to exit")
print("Otherwise, press any key to continue...")

local _,_,char = event.pull("key_down")
if char==string.byte("e") then
  require("computer").shutdown()
end

fullStop()

::main::
term.clear()
print("Brake: " .. brake)
print("Throttle: " .. throttle)

local _,_,char = event.pull("key_down")
if char==string.byte("1") then
  decreaseBrake()
elseif char==string.byte("4") then
  zeroBrake()
elseif char==string.byte("7") then
  increaseBrake()
elseif char==string.byte("2") then
  decreaseThrottle()
elseif char==string.byte("5") then
  zeroThrottle()
elseif char==string.byte("8") then
  increaseThrottle()
elseif char==string.byte("0") then
  fullStop()
end

if char~=string.byte("e") then
  goto main
end

require("computer").shutdown()

function goTo(x, y, z) 
    xPos, yPos, zPos = gps.locate();

    while xPos ~= x and yPos ~= y and zPos ~= z do
        xDir = (x - xpos) % 1
        yDir = (y - ypos) % 1
        zDir = (z - zpos) % 1
        for i = 1, math.abs(y - ypos), 1 do
            refuel()
            success = false
            if yDir == 1 then
                success = turtle.up()
                if not success then
                    turtle.digUp()
                end
            else 
                success = turtle.down()
                if not success then
                    turtle.digDown()
                end
            end
        end

        xPos, yPos, zPos = gps.locate();
    end
end

implement a multilevel feedback queue scheduling algorithm Queue A implements FCFS Round Robin. • Qu
content:
class Process:
    def __init__(self, name, arrival_time, burst_time):
        self.name = name
        self.arrival_time = arrival_time
        self.burst_time = burst_time
        self.remaining_time = burst_time


def multilevel_feedback_queue(processes, quantum_a, quantum_b):
    queue_a = []  # FCFS queue
    queue_b = []  # Round Robin queue

    time = 0
    completed_processes = []

    while processes or queue_a or queue_b:
        # Move processes to appropriate queues based on arrival time
        while processes and processes[0].arrival_time <= time:
            process = processes.pop(0)
            queue_a.append(process)

        # Execute processes in Queue A (FCFS)
        if queue_a:
            current_process = queue_a.pop(0)
            if current_process.remaining_time <= quantum_a:
                time += current_process.remaining_time
                current_process.remaining_time = 0
                completed_processes.append(current_process)
            else:
                time += quantum_a
                current_process.remaining_time -= quantum_a
                queue_b.append(current_process)

        # Execute processes in Queue B (Round Robin)
        elif queue_b:
            current_process = queue_b.pop(0)
            if current_process.remaining_time <= quantum_b:
                time += current_process.remaining_time
                current_process.remaining_time = 0
                completed_processes.append(current_process)
            else:
                time += quantum_b
                current_process.remaining_time -= quantum_b
                queue_b.append(current_process)

    # Calculate average waiting time and turnaround time
    waiting_time = sum(process.arrival_time for process in completed_processes)
    turnaround_time = sum(
        process.arrival_time + process.burst_time for process in completed_processes
    )
    avg_waiting_time = waiting_time / len(completed_processes)
    avg_turnaround_time = turnaround_time / len(completed_processes)

    return avg_waiting_time, avg_turnaround_time


# Example usage:
processes_multilevel = [
    Process("P1", 0, 24),
    Process("P2", 1, 3),
    Process("P3", 2, 3),
    # Add more processes as needed
]

quantum_a = 5
quantum_b = 20

avg_waiting_time, avg_turnaround_time = multilevel_feedback_queue(
    processes_multilevel, quantum_a, quantum_b
)

print("Multi-Level Feedback Queue:")
print(f"Average Waiting Time: {avg_waiting_time}")
print(f"Average Turnaround Time: {avg_turnaround_time}")

title: round robin that is fcfs with time quantum 5
content:
def round_robin_fcfs(processes, time_quantum):
    n = len(processes)
    burst_time = [process[2] for process in processes]

    # Initialize waiting time and turnaround time arrays
    waiting_time = [0] * n
    turnaround_time = [0] * n

    # Initialize remaining time for each process
    remaining_time = burst_time.copy()

    time = 0  # Current time
    for i in range(n):
        # If the process arrives later than the current time, wait for it
        if processes[i][1] > time:
            time = processes[i][1]

        # Execute the process for the given time quantum or until it completes
        current_burst = min(remaining_time[i], time_quantum)
        waiting_time[i] = time
        time += current_burst
        remaining_time[i] -= current_burst

        # If the process is not finished, put it at the end of the queue
        if remaining_time[i] > 0:
            processes.append(processes[i])

        turnaround_time[i] = time

    # Calculate average waiting time and turnaround time
    avg_waiting_time = sum(waiting_time) / n
    avg_turnaround_time = sum(turnaround_time) / n

    return avg_waiting_time, avg_turnaround_time


# Example usage:
processes_rr_fcfs = [
    ("P1", 0, 24),
    ("P2", 1, 3),
    ("P3", 2, 3),
]

time_quantum_rr_fcfs = 5

avg_waiting_time_rr_fcfs, avg_turnaround_time_rr_fcfs = round_robin_fcfs(processes_rr_fcfs, time_quantum_rr_fcfs)

print("Round Robin (FCFS with Time Quantum 5):")
print(f"Average Waiting Time: {avg_waiting_time_rr_fcfs}")
print(f"Average Turnaround Time: {avg_turnaround_time_rr_fcfs}")

function getTime()
    x = os.time()
    y = x%1
    affiche(x,y)
end

function affiche(x,y)
    c = peripheral.wrap("front")
	c.clear()
    a,b = c.getSize()
    
    a = math.floor(a/4)
    a2 = math.floor(a*3)
    b = math.floor(b/2)
    
    c.setCursorPos(a,b)
	x = x-y+6
	if x >= 24 then
		x = x - 24
	end
    c.write(x)
    
    c.setCursorPos(a2,b)
	y = math.floor(y * 60)
    c.write(y)
	os.sleep(1)
end

while true do
    getTime()
end
